  "wikitext": "\n'''4-3-320\n\nAlternative term: Anti-clutter rain, Fast time constant (F.T.C.) (U.S.A.), Short time constant (S.T.C.) (G.B.)\n\nA type of coupling circuit, with high pass frequency characteristics, used in radar receivers to permit discrimination against received pulses of duration longer than the transmitted pulse.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Differentiator}}\n[[Category:4.3 Radar, Radar Beacons and Radar Reflectors]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2023 Revision]]"
